decks.notes: The key concept of this Aggro-Affinity deck is to quickly and aggressively drop artifact creatures and other artifacts on the battlefield to overwhelm the opponent. By utilizing cards like Emry, Lurker of the Loch, Mishra's Bauble, Mox Opal, and Urza's Saga, the deck aims to generate fast mana and card advantage. The deck also includes disruption tools like Metallic Rebuke and Pithing Needle to control the opponent's game plan. With a focus on efficient artifact synergies and a high tempo playstyle, the deck aims to quickly close out games before the opponent can stabilize.

This deck focuses on disrupting your opponent's game plan while applying pressure with aggressive creatures. It utilizes cards like Thoughtseize and Prismatic Ending to disrupt the opponent's hand and board state, while also using cards like Ephemerate to blink creatures for additional value. The deck aims to control the board with removal spells like Fatal Push and Solitude, while also using powerful creatures like Overlord of the Balemurk and Ketramose, the New Dawn to close out the game quickly. Additionally, the deck includes graveyard hate with Relic of Progenitus to disrupt any graveyard strategies from the opponent.

This deck focuses on utilizing powerful Eldrazi creatures to quickly overwhelm the opponent and deal a large amount of damage in a short amount of time. By using cards like Chalice of the Void to disrupt the opponent's game plan and Kozilek's Command to control the board, the goal is to establish a dominant presence on the battlefield early on. With a mix of aggressive creatures and mana acceleration, this deck aims to apply pressure and force the opponent to react quickly or risk being overrun by the Eldrazi horde.
